-- Finmeccanica net up with gains
-- 
-- Tue May 13, 2008 2:54am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/13/us-finmeccanica-results-idUSMAT00817920080513

 

 MILAN  (Reuters) - Italian aerospace and defense company Finmeccanica SpA ( SIFI.MI ) posted a first-quarter net profit of 126 million euros ($194.7 million), up 563 percent from the prior year after one-time gains. 

 The net profit includes a capital gain from the sale of shares in chip maker STMicroelectronics NV ( STM.PA ). Excluding the gain, net profit was 72 million euros, the company said in a statement on Tuesday. Earnings before interest, tax and amortization (EBITA) were up 13 percent at 133 million euros. Finmeccanica confirmed its 2008 outlook, with organic revenue growth between 6 percent and 11 percent and adjusted EBITA increasing between 12 percent and 19 percent. (Reporting by  Ian Simpson )